description: Iceberg A23a — equivalent to the size of Rhode Island — has been near the South Orkney Islands since January, completing one full rotation every 24 days or so.
title: The world's largest iceberg is stuck twirling in an ocean vortex

description: Thomas Bach's tenure as Olympics leader has been controversial as took the IOC through doping scandals, controversy involving Chinese and Russian influence, and two Games held during Covid pandemic.
title: Thomas Bach who led the Olympic Games in sport and controversy will leave after 2025

description: Efforts to bring back the critically endangered red wolves are showing optimistic signs of some success.
title: Endangered red wolf population on the rebound with captive breeding program

description: The recent hostage swap with the Kremlin raises questions about the risks of future detentions.
title: What does the future of hostage diplomacy look like?

description: California Governor Gavin Newsom has threatened local county governments with funding cuts if they don't do enough to get people off the street. He recently passed an executive order encouraging local governments to remove homeless encampments.
title: California Governor threatens funding cuts for counties that don't remove homeless encampments

description: NPR's Pien Huang speaks to Ashley Jackson, co-director of the Center on Armed Groups, about the role of Islamic State affiliate groups on the recent foiled attacks on a Taylor Swift concert in Vienna.
title: The role of Islamic State affiliated groups on foiled attacks in Vienna

description: In a photo finish, Masai Russell of the U.S. captured a gold medal in the hundred-meter hurdle sprint, beating a French runner by 0.01 seconds.
title: American Masai Russell wins Olympic gold in 100m hurdles by a 100th of a second
